James seeks advice on the criteria for a successful wrongful termination case after his wife was fired. Arachne provides a comprehensive overview of the basic criteria, including employment contract violation, unlawful termination, public policy violation, constructive dismissal, and an implied promise. Arachne advises James to consult with an attorney due to variations in laws across different jurisdictions. She also highlights the potential costs, length of legal proceedings, emotional stress, and reputation impact that should be considered before taking legal action.
